The paper deals with revenue maximization in auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The use of linear programming duality and complementarity suggests a connection to mathematical programming (cs.IT) and optimization. The application of the framework to a multiple-good monopoly setting involves the use of algorithms and mechanism design (cs.AI, cs.EC).
